{{Infobox person | name = Zelma O'Neal | image = | imagesize = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date ={{Birth date|1903|05|29|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Rock Falls, Illinois]], U.S. | death_date = {{Death date |1989|11|03|df=yes}} | death_place = [[Largo, Florida]], U.S. | other_names = | occupation = Actress | years_active = 1927 - 1937 | spouse = | partner = | website = }} '''Zelma O'Neal''' (May 29, 1903 - November 3, 1989) was an actress, singer, and dancer in the 1920s and 1930s. She appeared on [[Broadway theatre|Broadway]] and in early [[sound film]]s, including the [[Paramount Pictures]] films ''[[Paramount on Parade]]'' and ''[[Follow Thru]]'' (both 1930).<ref name=imdboneal>{{IMDb name|641952|Zelma O'Neal}}</ref>
She was married to actor [[Anthony Bushell]] from 1928-1935. He said in the 1990s that he ended the marriage because he wanted a joint career but she wanted to be a society hostess. He also claimed to have been married three times, which does not seem to have been the case.
==Selected filmography== * ''[[Mister Cinders (film)|Mister Cinders]]'' (1934) * ''[[Freedom of the Seas (film)|Freedom of the Seas]]'' (1934) * ''[[There Goes Susie]]'' (1934) * ''[[Spring in the Air]]'' (1934) * ''[[Joy Ride (1934 film)|Joy Ride]]'' (1934) * ''[[Give Her a Ring]]'' (1936) * ''[[Let's Make a Night of It]]'' (1938)
